WEBVTT

00:04.235 --> 00:07.108
Come on, Miley, the sooner
we get to Traci's party,

00:07.108 --> 00:10.541
the sooner we can, you know,
leave Traci's party.

00:11.682 --> 00:14.185
If you hate her so much,
why are you going?

00:14.185 --> 00:16.517
[beeps]

00:16.517 --> 00:20.391
Because her food is
fantastic and I lined
my purse with plastic.

00:20.391 --> 00:22.693
That is so tacky.

00:22.693 --> 00:24.525
And get me anything
wrapped in bacon.

00:26.697 --> 00:29.400
Ow! There's glitter in my eye,
glitter in my eye!

00:29.400 --> 00:31.802
Well, at least this time
your wig isn't itching.

00:31.802 --> 00:34.465
You had to go there!

00:34.465 --> 00:36.667
Well, now you're not thinking
about the glitter in your eye.

00:36.667 --> 00:38.809
Ah!

00:38.809 --> 00:40.541
[groaning]

00:40.541 --> 00:42.573
- [crash]
- Ow!

00:45.576 --> 00:47.618
Hey, Dad, we're off to Traci's.
See you in a little bit.

00:47.618 --> 00:50.151
- Hey, bring me back...
- Anything wrapped in bacon.

00:50.151 --> 00:51.152
Got it.

00:52.553 --> 00:54.425
So this is pretty much
your Saturday night?

00:54.425 --> 00:56.157
Heck no. After this,

00:56.157 --> 00:58.559
I'm gonna write the
account numbers on the rolls.

00:58.559 --> 01:01.432
Edgar down at the bank
appreciates my thoroughness.

01:01.432 --> 01:03.564
Good for you.

01:05.696 --> 01:08.068
Come on! I wanna get there
before Lady Gaga

01:08.068 --> 01:10.441
turns the dessert table
into a hat.

01:12.443 --> 01:15.706
Come on now,
you gotta get in there.

01:15.706 --> 01:20.311
[high-pitched] No, no,
the other quarters hate me
'cause I'm shiny.

01:20.311 --> 01:23.214
We have got to get
my dad a girlfriend.

01:25.316 --> 01:26.657
[Miley] Whoo!

01:26.657 --> 01:29.120
Here we go, everybody!

01:30.321 --> 01:31.592
♪ Come on ♪

01:31.592 --> 01:34.265
♪ You get the limo
out front ♪

01:34.265 --> 01:35.866
♪ Oooh ♪

01:35.866 --> 01:39.270
♪ Hottest styles
Every shoe, every color ♪

01:39.270 --> 01:43.334
♪ Yeah, when you're famous
it can be kind of fun ♪

01:43.334 --> 01:47.678
♪ It's really you
but no one ever discovers ♪

01:47.678 --> 01:51.612
♪ Who would have thought
that a girl like me ♪

01:51.612 --> 01:55.816
♪ Would double
as a superstar ♪

01:55.816 --> 01:57.518
Whooo!

01:57.518 --> 02:01.492
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

02:01.492 --> 02:03.494
♪ Chill it out
Take it slow ♪

02:03.494 --> 02:04.825
♪ Then you rock out the show ♪

02:04.825 --> 02:09.229
♪ You get the best
of both worlds ♪

02:09.229 --> 02:11.702
♪ Mix it all together
and you know ♪

02:11.702 --> 02:14.765
♪ That it's the best
of both worlds ♪♪

02:18.769 --> 02:22.273
♪ Ooh, oh ♪

02:22.273 --> 02:26.417
Stupid dumb party. Big empty
purse, wasted use of plastic.

02:26.417 --> 02:28.519
Oh, will you stop muttering?

02:28.519 --> 02:30.821
You drag me
to Traci's dumb party,

02:30.821 --> 02:33.524
and then make me leave before
I can load up on cream puffs.

02:33.524 --> 02:35.386
Huh? Empty. Empty.

02:35.386 --> 02:37.788
Oh, I'm sorry.
I think you meant to say,

02:37.788 --> 02:40.391
"Gee, Miley, I'm really
worried about your dad, too.

02:40.391 --> 02:41.532
Maybe we should go
home and hang out

02:41.532 --> 02:43.464
with the sweet and
desperately lonely man

02:43.464 --> 02:45.466
that gives me
my food and shelter."

02:45.466 --> 02:46.567
Or something like that.

02:47.798 --> 02:49.270
Yeah, OK.

02:49.270 --> 02:51.542
But I'm a lot more compassionate
after a cream puff!

02:52.443 --> 02:54.405
Lilly!

02:54.405 --> 02:57.478
- Uh, Dad?
- Shh! For goodness sakes,
this is important!

02:57.478 --> 02:59.450
[woman on TV] And my
last rose goes to...

02:59.450 --> 03:01.552
Pick Michael,
pick Michael, pick Michael!

03:01.552 --> 03:03.684
- [woman] Michael.
- Whoo-hoo! Yeah!

03:03.684 --> 03:05.556
Tell you what.
I didn't like him at first,

03:05.556 --> 03:07.187
but after he read
that kitty cat poem,

03:07.187 --> 03:08.689
I was Team Michael all the way.

03:08.689 --> 03:10.491
Dad, you can't live like this.

03:10.491 --> 03:12.423
When was the last time
you had a date?

03:12.423 --> 03:14.325
Oh, for Pete's sake, darlin'.

03:14.325 --> 03:17.228
You don't have to worry
about my love life.

03:17.228 --> 03:19.730
Translation: a long time ago.

03:19.730 --> 03:22.433
I'll tell you what. Ol' Robby
Ray will date somebody

03:22.433 --> 03:24.475
when he meets somebody
he wants to date.

03:24.475 --> 03:26.577
That's the way
Robby Ray rolls.

03:26.577 --> 03:28.579
Well, unless her name
is Day Old Pizza,

03:28.579 --> 03:31.242
I don't see it happening.

03:31.242 --> 03:33.644
- [sighs]
- What are you getting
so freaked out about?

03:33.644 --> 03:36.387
You heard the guy. He'll date
someone when he's ready.

03:36.387 --> 03:38.989
Yeah, but what
if he never is?

03:49.730 --> 03:51.802
Dangflammit!

03:51.802 --> 03:54.735
Hold still, you little
son of a pepperoni!

03:59.640 --> 04:01.772
- Miley?
- Sorry.

04:01.772 --> 04:04.345
I'm not gonna
let my dad end up alone.

04:04.345 --> 04:07.418
[sighs] When you say "I,"
you mean "we," don't you?

04:07.418 --> 04:10.020
Share the bedroom,
share the life.

04:10.020 --> 04:13.624
♪ Whoa, oh, oh ♪

04:15.626 --> 04:18.559
Hey, Mamaw, just called
to see how you're doing.

04:19.630 --> 04:21.432
You broke your leg skiing?

04:21.432 --> 04:22.693
I'm sorry.

04:22.693 --> 04:24.965
You know who doesn't
have a broken leg?

04:24.965 --> 04:27.498
The supermodel I'm dating.

04:27.498 --> 04:30.771
That's right,
I'm dating a supermodel!

04:30.771 --> 04:34.575
- [doorbell rings]
- Gotta go.
Hope your arm's feeling better.

04:34.575 --> 04:35.646
Yeah, yeah, leg, whatever.

04:38.679 --> 04:42.453
OK, I want an answer
and I want it right now!

04:43.814 --> 04:47.518
How can a girl like... this

04:47.518 --> 04:50.721
be with a guy like... this?

04:52.663 --> 04:54.595
That's not fair.
Anybody can look stupid

04:54.595 --> 04:56.567
if you catch
them at the wrong time.

04:56.567 --> 04:58.469
Well...

05:01.572 --> 05:04.074
It was a really cheesy pizza!

05:06.737 --> 05:09.009
It was a really muggy day!

05:13.844 --> 05:16.347
That is not me!

05:16.347 --> 05:18.889
Now, I can see her
going out with you once.

05:18.889 --> 05:20.951
She lost a bet, pity date

05:20.951 --> 05:23.694
or the whole "I'm trying
to punish my parents" thing.

05:24.855 --> 05:26.096
But three weeks?!

05:26.096 --> 05:27.698
It makes no sense.

05:27.698 --> 05:30.431
You're not good-looking,
you're not smart

05:30.431 --> 05:32.703
and you pick your nose
behind the menu.

05:32.703 --> 05:33.604
I do not!

05:34.635 --> 05:37.968
I don't need
to see the pictures!

05:37.968 --> 05:41.111
So, what are you, the world's
greatest kisser or something?

05:41.111 --> 05:44.114
Well, yeah, that's me.

05:44.114 --> 05:48.449
Mr. World's
Greatest Kisser... Guy.

05:49.850 --> 05:51.582
Well, OK.
Thanks for coming by.

05:51.582 --> 05:54.625
We should do this again
real soon. Bye-bye.

05:59.990 --> 06:01.732
You haven't kissed her yet!

06:01.732 --> 06:05.736
[scoffs] Yes, I have.

06:05.736 --> 06:08.739
No, you haven't! That's why
she hasn't broken up with you.

06:08.739 --> 06:12.142
This is a girl who's kissed
football players, rock stars,

06:12.142 --> 06:16.607
Australians!
You know, real men.

06:17.608 --> 06:20.010
And once she kisses you,

06:20.010 --> 06:21.752
you can kiss her goodbye!

06:21.752 --> 06:24.915
Finally, my world
makes sense again.

06:29.420 --> 06:32.062
No, no, no!

06:35.696 --> 06:39.830
♪ Yeah, yeah, ooh ♪

06:41.532 --> 06:43.804
Hi, there.
Are those for the bake sale?

06:43.804 --> 06:46.937
Those look delish. My single
daddy would love those.

06:48.108 --> 06:50.781
- What's your recipe?
- Wedding ring.

06:50.781 --> 06:52.543
Move along.

06:53.784 --> 06:54.845
Hi.

06:54.845 --> 06:57.187
Those for the bake sale?
They look delicious.

06:57.187 --> 07:00.521
- Dating anyone special?
- Why, yes, I am.

07:00.521 --> 07:04.795
- My husband.
- Would it kill you
to wear a ring?

07:06.196 --> 07:08.699
Are there no divorced
mothers in this school?

07:08.699 --> 07:11.131
It's California,
for cryin' out loud.

07:11.131 --> 07:13.664
Come on. We'll find somebody.
Stop wigging out.

07:13.664 --> 07:16.667
And the phantom
wig itch returns.

07:16.667 --> 07:19.810
Are there no good single men
left in this city?

07:19.810 --> 07:22.212
He had no manners,
wasn't into music,

07:22.212 --> 07:24.675
and when I complimented him
on his hair,

07:24.675 --> 07:27.578
he took it off to show me
where he bought it.

07:28.879 --> 07:31.952
I'll never get that sound of
ripping Velcro out of my head.

07:31.952 --> 07:35.155
[imitates ripping] Ew!

07:36.757 --> 07:38.689
Well, Daddy did say
bring him back

07:38.689 --> 07:40.561
something from the bake sale.

07:42.032 --> 07:45.135
No, Mother, I will not
go out with your butcher

07:45.135 --> 07:46.837
so you can get free meat.

07:48.839 --> 07:52.603
Fifty percent off king crab?

07:52.603 --> 07:55.776
No, Mom, no. I'm not gonna
do it. I have my pride.

07:55.776 --> 07:58.108
Mom, you know what?
I gotta go.

07:58.108 --> 08:02.853
There's a sick kid in my office.
Listen. [fake coughing]

08:02.853 --> 08:05.886
Hear that, Mom?
Oh, so sorry. Gotta go. Bye.

08:08.619 --> 08:10.721
- Is this a bad time?
- [groans] No.

08:10.721 --> 08:13.894
- My mom's just wiggin' out.
- Again with that word.

08:15.926 --> 08:17.868
I need to talk to you about
something a little awkward

08:17.868 --> 08:21.872
- and potentially embarrassing.
- Miley, relax.

08:23.934 --> 08:26.877
I'm a nurse.
I've seen it all.

08:26.877 --> 08:29.509
Uh, not that kind of awkward
and embarrassing.

08:29.509 --> 08:32.042
Miley, it's OK. You're not the
first senior to get head lice.

08:32.042 --> 08:35.885
- Um, I don't have head lice.
- Let's hope not.
Just sit still.

08:35.885 --> 08:37.047
- But...
- Miley!

08:37.047 --> 08:39.890
Fine.

08:39.890 --> 08:43.654
Well, I sure hope
I don't have head lice,

08:43.654 --> 08:47.227
because then my single
and very attractive daddy

08:47.227 --> 08:48.959
would have to come pick me up.

08:48.959 --> 08:51.632
I'm pretty sure you'd be able
to drive yourself home.

08:51.632 --> 08:53.764
Yeah, you're right.

08:53.764 --> 08:57.708
Besides, I bet he's really
busy working on his music

08:57.708 --> 09:00.110
and brushing his incredibly
beautiful and real hair

09:00.110 --> 09:03.644
or, you know, perhaps
practicing opening doors

09:03.644 --> 09:05.716
for a future girlfriend
he hopes to have one day.

09:07.848 --> 09:10.050
All right. Miley.
What's going on?

09:10.050 --> 09:12.853
Well, I kinda heard
your conversation
in the cafeteria,

09:12.853 --> 09:15.826
- and my dad's single...
- Oh! Whoa, whoa.

09:15.826 --> 09:18.058
Hold it right there.
That's very sweet of you,

09:18.058 --> 09:20.991
but I'm through with fix-ups.
From now on,

09:20.991 --> 09:23.694
I will date someone when
I meet someone I wanna date.

09:23.694 --> 09:26.336
That's exactly what my dad
said! You have got to meet him!

09:28.338 --> 09:30.671
She won't meet him.

09:30.671 --> 09:33.704
Well, I guess there is
just nothing else we can do,

09:33.704 --> 09:36.576
- she said hopefully.
- She was wrong.

09:36.576 --> 09:38.979
I know they'd like each other
if I could just get them
in the same room.

09:38.979 --> 09:41.852
All right, but don't
drag me into it.

09:41.852 --> 09:43.954
- Fine.
- [dials phone]

09:43.954 --> 09:46.617
Hey, Dad, you gotta get down
to the nurse's office.

09:46.617 --> 09:49.690
Lilly's got the cold sweats
and shakes.

09:49.690 --> 09:53.694
What're you talking about?
[gasps] No!

09:53.694 --> 09:56.727
Sorry, involuntary
muscle spasm.

09:56.727 --> 09:58.829
Don't wanna have lunch with me.

10:03.834 --> 10:07.978
♪ Ooh, ah, oh ♪

10:07.978 --> 10:11.611
No, this one does not sound
better than Velcro Head.

10:11.611 --> 10:15.716
Mother, I'm not
playing hard to get.
First, he's 73.

10:15.716 --> 10:18.388
And second, he's 73.
I gotta go.

10:18.388 --> 10:22.923
- OK... Let's see.
- [coughing]

10:22.923 --> 10:26.857
Well, no fever
and your sweats are gone.

10:26.857 --> 10:28.999
Are you sure there's
nothing else making you sick?

10:28.999 --> 10:30.861
Maybe like your mother?

10:30.861 --> 10:34.665
Maybe it was
something I ate. Ooh!

10:36.066 --> 10:39.740
Um, you know, I can feel
those shakes coming back.

10:39.740 --> 10:42.773
[stammering] Can I please
get a blanket?

10:42.773 --> 10:44.745
Hm... OK.

10:53.653 --> 10:55.686
[gasping]

10:59.159 --> 11:00.831
Here's your blanket.

11:04.895 --> 11:06.036
Hm...

11:07.838 --> 11:10.771
And your sweats
are back, too.

11:10.771 --> 11:12.903
And they smell
like mango iced tea.

11:15.445 --> 11:19.449
Must be one of those,
uh, tropical viruses.

11:20.781 --> 11:23.784
The nurse is busy.
It's a stomachache. Man up!

11:25.455 --> 11:29.860
- [retching]
- Oh, no!
Watch the boots, buddy!

11:29.860 --> 11:31.862
- How's Lilly doing?
- Not very good.

11:31.862 --> 11:33.824
You should go
talk to the nurse.

11:33.824 --> 11:35.465
Wait, wait, wait.

11:38.068 --> 11:39.129
Go talk to her.

11:40.070 --> 11:42.202
Hi, I'm here for, uh...

11:44.805 --> 11:48.078
- Uh...
- Lilly Truscott.

11:48.078 --> 11:49.339
Right, her.

11:50.080 --> 11:51.812
Right, her.

11:51.812 --> 11:56.246
Look at that. I'm just
feeling so much...

11:56.246 --> 11:57.347
See you later.

12:01.491 --> 12:05.155
- Hi, I'm Lori.
- I'm, uh...

12:05.155 --> 12:07.357
- Robby!
- Robby. That guy.

12:07.357 --> 12:09.830
- [laughing] Hi.
- Robby.

12:14.234 --> 12:16.236
Prepare to be kissed

12:16.236 --> 12:18.969
as you've never
been kissed before.

12:32.983 --> 12:36.056
I bet an Australian never
kissed you like that before.

12:37.928 --> 12:42.392
Blech! Yuck! Seriously?! Ugh!

12:44.034 --> 12:46.797
No, wait, I can do better!

12:46.797 --> 12:48.138
I'm... I'm...

12:48.138 --> 12:50.801
Begging the piggy
for a second chance?

12:50.801 --> 12:53.003
[laughing hysterically]

12:56.877 --> 12:58.809
[grunting]

13:01.481 --> 13:02.813
[doorbell rings]

13:05.785 --> 13:07.317
Siena! Hey!

13:07.317 --> 13:09.960
Hey, hey. Um...

13:09.960 --> 13:11.561
What are you doing here?

13:11.561 --> 13:13.423
Well, it's just,
we had such a good time
the other night,

13:13.423 --> 13:15.926
and you haven't
called, so...

13:15.926 --> 13:19.830
- Is everything OK?
- OK? Everything's great.

13:19.830 --> 13:21.902
In fact, I was
just getting ready to call you.

13:21.902 --> 13:24.935
So maybe you should go home,
and I'll call you right now.

13:24.935 --> 13:27.838
- [laughs]
- Better hurry, or it's
just gonna be a message.

13:27.838 --> 13:30.110
You are so funny.

13:34.384 --> 13:35.916
Uh...

13:35.916 --> 13:38.048
So who wants to watch TV?

13:39.089 --> 13:40.851
I'm gonna make some popcorn.

13:40.851 --> 13:42.953
You like popcorn, I like
popcorn. I'll make some popcorn.

13:42.953 --> 13:45.926
It's gonna give us something
to do with our mouths.

13:45.926 --> 13:50.060
It's not really my
first choice, but OK.

13:52.062 --> 13:53.333
Ooh!

13:55.505 --> 13:59.940
Who's this? My competition?

13:59.940 --> 14:01.972
[laughs] Who's
the funny one now?

14:06.947 --> 14:09.479
[music plays on TV]

14:11.952 --> 14:15.225
I can't wait to see this.
I've heard it's so romantic.

14:15.225 --> 14:17.357
Well, alrighty then.

14:26.496 --> 14:29.099
Well, alrighty then.

14:31.271 --> 14:33.243
[laughs]

14:37.507 --> 14:42.512
Ooh! I'm kinda chilly,
aren't you?

14:42.512 --> 14:44.514
- Now that you mention it, I am.
- Yeah?

14:47.187 --> 14:48.518
Thanks.

14:51.591 --> 14:53.423
Ah! It's toasty.

14:56.066 --> 14:58.028
Well, alrighty then.

15:23.223 --> 15:27.227
Wow! The bass sounds
great down here.

15:27.227 --> 15:29.459
I feel so stupid.
You just wanna be friends,

15:29.459 --> 15:31.201
and I'm throwing myself at you.

15:32.362 --> 15:34.934
This is so embarrassing!

15:34.934 --> 15:36.436
Siena, wait!

15:37.337 --> 15:38.708
No, wait!

15:42.572 --> 15:44.514
Wait, I do. I wanna...

15:45.575 --> 15:47.177
I wanna be

15:47.177 --> 15:48.448
more than just friends.

15:48.448 --> 15:54.084
Then why
won't you kiss me?

15:54.084 --> 15:57.087
'Cause I'm not like the guys
you usually go out with.

15:58.588 --> 16:00.991
They're all...

16:00.991 --> 16:03.593
[growls]

16:03.593 --> 16:06.066
And I'm... eh...

16:07.337 --> 16:09.099
They're all... Ho, ho!

16:09.099 --> 16:11.341
And I'm... hey...

16:14.144 --> 16:15.745
You're right.

16:15.745 --> 16:17.547
You're not like the guys I date.

16:19.249 --> 16:21.681
You are...

16:23.613 --> 16:25.215
...way better.

16:36.266 --> 16:38.368
- Whoa!
- [crashing]

16:38.368 --> 16:41.371
♪ La-di-da-da-da ♪

16:43.103 --> 16:46.776
Again, you don't have
enough for the big tiger, OK?

16:46.776 --> 16:51.241
It's the dragon stickers,
the eraser or the ice cube
with the fly in it.

16:54.244 --> 16:56.186
Thank you!

16:56.186 --> 16:57.287
Oh, hey.

16:57.287 --> 17:00.120
I thought you'd be spying
on your dad and his date.

17:00.120 --> 17:01.391
It's not like
I'm 12 anymore.

17:01.391 --> 17:03.253
Like I'm gonna follow
them to some restaurant,

17:03.253 --> 17:06.126
hide behind a potted plant,
then get underneath
a dessert cart

17:06.126 --> 17:09.529
when I can't
hear them anymore. Please!

17:09.529 --> 17:12.801
- Did you get me a cream puff?
- No, but I did get a crème
brûlée and a chocolate mousse.

17:14.263 --> 17:16.205
- Yeah!
- The good thing is

17:16.205 --> 17:18.407
they're having an awesome time
and they didn't see me.

17:18.407 --> 17:20.440
Yeah.

17:20.440 --> 17:22.412
- Well, they're
gonna see you now.
- Yoinks!

17:22.412 --> 17:26.045
- Whoo!
- Hey, guys!

17:26.045 --> 17:28.218
What are ya'll doing here?
Oh, that's right.

17:28.218 --> 17:29.749
You two kids are on a date.

17:29.749 --> 17:32.452
I completely forgot,
slipped my mind.

17:32.452 --> 17:35.585
Yeah, we went to that
really nice fish place
down at the end of the pier.

17:35.585 --> 17:38.288
You know the one. The one
with the dessert carts

17:38.288 --> 17:40.760
big enough for a girl
to hide under.

17:40.760 --> 17:43.433
Except her feet
kind of poke out the back.

17:45.195 --> 17:46.766
Nope, doesn't ring a bell.

17:46.766 --> 17:50.100
Well, then, maybe this
might jog your memory.

17:50.100 --> 17:51.841
You owe me for a crème brûlée,

17:51.841 --> 17:54.244
a chocolate mousse
and a cream puff.

17:54.244 --> 17:57.477
- Cream puff? You said...
- I was hungry!

17:57.477 --> 18:00.310
Miley, relax,
we're having a good time.

18:00.310 --> 18:03.613
- A great time.
- A great time.

18:03.613 --> 18:06.656
See, the old man's still
got a little giddy-up
in his git along.

18:08.318 --> 18:10.089
I cannot believe you
lied about the cream puff.

18:10.089 --> 18:12.462
- Who cares about
the cream puff?
- Me!

18:12.462 --> 18:15.225
Look, they're having
a great time.

18:15.225 --> 18:17.727
Do I have a gift of knowing
when people are right
for each other or what?

18:17.727 --> 18:20.130
You never thought me and Oliver
were right for each other.

18:20.130 --> 18:22.272
- The jury's still out
on that one.
- I'm sorry, what?

18:22.272 --> 18:24.103
Fine.

18:24.103 --> 18:25.875
I give you permission
to say one bad thing about Jake.

18:25.875 --> 18:27.137
He looks like Ellen DeGeneres.

18:27.137 --> 18:30.740
That is so...
freakishly true.

18:30.740 --> 18:32.882
Get that out of
your head, Miley.
Get that out of your head!

18:32.882 --> 18:35.245
Think about your dad
and how happy he is.

18:35.245 --> 18:39.289
He's laughing,
they're holding hands
in line for a roller coaster!

18:39.289 --> 18:40.890
Oh, my gosh!

18:40.890 --> 18:44.254
- Why am I saying,
"Oh, my gosh?"
- Two years ago, Fourth of July.

18:44.254 --> 18:45.825
Remember?

18:47.497 --> 18:49.429
- I don't see it. Oh.
- Right here.

18:53.803 --> 18:56.306
[all] Whoo!

18:57.837 --> 19:00.410
Oh, Lord! Ah!

19:00.410 --> 19:03.243
[shouting]

19:03.243 --> 19:04.714
Oh, my gosh! Oh, my gosh!

19:04.714 --> 19:06.576
If she hears that
crazy coaster cackle,

19:06.576 --> 19:08.648
she's gonna dump him
quicker than I dump Jake

19:08.648 --> 19:12.322
if I can't get that dang Ellen
DeGeneres thing out of my head,
thank you so much!

19:12.322 --> 19:17.187
♪ Oh, oh
Hey, yeah ♪

19:17.187 --> 19:20.660
You know what I hate? People
who scream on roller coasters.

19:20.660 --> 19:23.563
I mean, it's not like you
don't know what's gonna happen.
You're up, down,

19:23.563 --> 19:25.465
you're around, you're done.
That's it.

19:25.465 --> 19:29.199
So let's just
not scream, OK? Sh!

19:29.199 --> 19:31.401
I thought you said Miley
was your normal kid.

19:31.401 --> 19:33.603
- Sadly, that's true.
- [laughs]

19:33.603 --> 19:36.476
OK, here we go! Remember,
it's cool to be quiet.

19:36.476 --> 19:39.409
- Let's all try it.
- Let's.

19:40.350 --> 19:43.883
[screaming]

19:44.454 --> 19:45.885
Get off, Mile!

19:45.885 --> 19:48.187
Sorry, Dad! Giving
you a hug from behind!

19:48.187 --> 19:50.290
- Love you!
- [muffled scream]

19:50.290 --> 19:51.961
[screaming]

19:51.961 --> 19:55.225
- Oh, Lord!
- I changed my mind!
Let's all scream!

19:55.225 --> 19:57.597
[all screaming]

20:05.235 --> 20:07.577
Whoo! That was so much fun!
You know what?

20:07.577 --> 20:10.510
That is the kind of fun
you cannot duplicate,
so let's make a pact right now

20:10.510 --> 20:12.342
that we will not get on
that roller coaster ever again

20:12.342 --> 20:14.584
because that would only cheapen
the fun we've shared.

20:14.584 --> 20:15.915
Who's with me?

20:15.915 --> 20:19.319
Put your hands in!

20:19.319 --> 20:21.791
I can't hear anything you say,
but I wanna ride it again!

20:21.791 --> 20:24.994
Me, too!
And without you this time.

20:24.994 --> 20:29.259
- And without her this time!
- No, no, no. You can't.
Excuse us.

20:29.259 --> 20:30.460
Why don't you
save us a spot in line?

20:30.460 --> 20:32.332
I'll go save us a spot in line!

20:35.935 --> 20:38.808
Mile, what in the Sam Hill
is going on with you, girl?

20:38.808 --> 20:41.871
- I just don't want
you to blow it.
- What?

20:41.871 --> 20:45.014
I've been trying hard
to get your quarter rollin'
rump out of the house,

20:45.014 --> 20:47.377
and now your crazy coaster
cackle is gonna blow it!

20:47.377 --> 20:51.351
- Crazy coaster what?
- Oh, Lord! Oh, Lord!

20:51.351 --> 20:55.425
- [grunting]
- Stop that.
People are lookin' at you

20:55.425 --> 20:57.287
like you're one apple
shy of a fritter.

20:57.287 --> 20:59.489
And that's exactly how
Lori's gonna look at you

20:59.489 --> 21:01.391
if you go
on that coaster again.

21:01.391 --> 21:03.393
I just don't want you
to die alone, Dad!

21:04.694 --> 21:06.296
Do you know
something I don't?

21:06.296 --> 21:07.637
Daddy, before you know it,

21:07.637 --> 21:09.268
Jackson and I are gonna
be out of the house

21:09.268 --> 21:11.771
- and you're gonna be...
- Just fine.

21:11.771 --> 21:14.674
Mile, one of the hardest
things a parent has to do

21:14.674 --> 21:18.778
is watch their child go off
on their own and trust
that they'll be OK.

21:18.778 --> 21:21.381
You're just gonna have to trust
that I'll be OK, too.

21:21.381 --> 21:23.913
- I know, Dad, but...
- Hey, honey.

21:23.913 --> 21:26.656
If your mama could accept me,
cackle and all,

21:26.656 --> 21:28.518
somebody else will, too.

21:28.518 --> 21:31.861
Maybe it's Lori,
maybe it's not.

21:31.861 --> 21:35.064
I'm gonna have to get on
that coaster and go find out.

21:35.064 --> 21:36.526
And you're just gonna
have to let me.

21:37.467 --> 21:39.329
Go get 'em, cowboy.

21:41.070 --> 21:42.071
Oh, wait.

21:45.074 --> 21:46.436
Wait.

21:48.538 --> 21:49.539
OK, go.

21:57.417 --> 21:58.948
They grow up so fast.

21:58.948 --> 22:00.950
♪ Oh, ah, ooh ♪

22:03.423 --> 22:06.496
♪ Hey, yeah ♪

22:07.497 --> 22:08.958
I'll see you girls later.

22:08.958 --> 22:11.361
Lori and I are
gonna go catch a movie.

22:11.361 --> 22:13.563
Don't wait up.
[clicks tongue]

22:13.563 --> 22:16.436
Who would've thought
Lori'd get over your
dad's coaster cackle?

22:16.436 --> 22:19.469
Yeah, and who thought
Siena'd get over Jackson's...

22:19.469 --> 22:20.440
Well, everything.

22:22.642 --> 22:24.574
Hey, we have
the house to ourselves.

22:24.574 --> 22:26.446
You're right.

22:26.446 --> 22:28.618
No dad, no annoying brother.

22:28.618 --> 22:31.451
We could do anything.

22:31.451 --> 22:33.853
[both] Pick Steven,
pick Steven, pick Steven!
